title: King Snake Roost Discography
description:
The complete Discography by Australian noise rock band King Snake Roost. They mixed raw, primitive, clumsy blues and jazz and referenced a multitude of styles, from Minutemen to Sonny Sharrock. Their third album, Ground Into the Dirt, is notable for being produced by Butch Vig (pre-Nirvana) and released by Amphetamine Reptile. The band played with some of the most influential noise rock bands of the 1980s, including Sonic Youth, Big Black, Mudhoney, Helmet, Babes In Toyland, Lubricated Goat, feedtime and The Mark of Cain.

contains:
(1987) From Barbarism to Christian Manhood
(1989) Things That Play Themselves
(1990) Ground Into the Dirt
